** How To use "routerLink" to load dynamic component **

step 1- create component 

step2 - In app.routing.module.ts -> Inside Routes Arrary -> create object eg.
       const Routes:Routes = [
        {
            path: 'registartion',  //path name
            component: Registartioncomponent
        },
         {
            path: 'home',  //path name
            component: Homecomponent
        }
       ]  

step 3- go to app.component.html -> make sure <router-outlet></router-outlet> is added 
      (if not available add it manually)

step 4 - then go to any component.html file where we want to add button or add navbar from bootstarp
      e.g navbar.component.html

      <button routerLink = "registartion" >Registration</button>

